    "prompt": "Write a poem.\n\nIt is March 30, 2026. The season is early autumn: first letting go, colors changing, temperatures dropping.\n\nToday felt like this: The way your body feels after a full day in the sun with almost nothing to drink. The feeling of a good day where your body just doesn't register the air at all. That neutral humidity of a good autumn day\u2014nothing to complain about. Like a settled autumn week with the same mild weather day after day. Like being in a cafe with small windows on a cloudy afternoon. Like a garden 7 days into a stable pattern\u2014just ticking along.\n\nThe poem should carry the feeling of thirsting / drought: urgent need, emptiness, craving, reaching, desiccation.\n\nCRITICAL: The poem MUST include clear language about the plant's moisture state. Use these words naturally: thirst, dry, parched, craving water, empty, depleted, drained. A visitor reading this poem should understand: \"NEEDS WATER NOW\".\n\nMake the moisture state EXPLICIT in the poem - not metaphorical. The plan"
  },
